The data in Table 3 explains the relationship of multiple correlations between metacognitive abilities, and autonomous learning with learning outcomes of the students in the Language and art majors in the Faculty of Teacher Training and Education of the Pattimura University. The calculation results illustrate that there is a significant relationship between learner autonomy, metacognition, and Indonesian language learning outcomes. This is seen from the results obtained by r count higher than the r table that is 0.808≥0.361. That means that there is a very significant relationship between autonomous learning, Metacognitive abilities, and Indonesian language learning outcomes. These results indicate that if students have high metacognitive abilities and are supported by the willingness to learn autonomously, then they will achieve better results.
